From 8f1aa46a5b98e8d996a5812220e9adcf07b865ca Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@tsm-consultz.local>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 20:58:34 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Cross-War Room Foundation Modules + fix stubbed control plane

Foundation gap fixed first: /js/core/tsm-event-bus.js and
tsm-mission-engine.js were 6-line placeholder stubs, not the real v1.1
implementations (which existed unreferenced at repo root, unreachable
by any server route). tsm-state.js real version never existed anywhere.
Net effect: O2C/CRM/Approval/CPQ war rooms were running on a no-op
event bus with no state layer. Replaced stubs with the real event-bus
and mission-engine, and wrote a real tsm-state.js implementing the
set/update/push/get contract both already depend on.

New: html/js/foundation/ -- 8 reusable modules any war room can load:
  tsm-kpi-cards.js        Universal KPI Cards (revenue/cost/sla/util/risk/quality/csat)
  tsm-decision-engine.js  AI Decision Engine client -- root cause, anomaly,
                          recommendation, impact, predictive alert modes
  tsm-workflow-engine.js  Configurable state machines, approvals, escalation
                          timers, notifications
  tsm-analytics-hub.js    groupBy/sum/avg/trend/drillDown + snapshot history
  tsm-collaboration.js    Comments, @mentions, task assignment, attachments,
                          meeting notes
  tsm-enterprise-search.js In-memory cross-source search (register any record array)
  tsm-governance.js       Role-based access, policy checks, audit trail reads
  tsm-integration-layer.js Connector registry w/ health checks + sync tracking

server.js: added POST /api/foundation/decision -- one generic AI route
keyed by vertical (reads SP[vertical]) + mode, so future phases don't
need a bespoke /api/{vertical}/query route copy-pasted each time.

war-rooms/o2c/o2c-war-room.html: wired as proof of concept. Moved
control-plane + foundation <script> tags before the inline script that
uses them (previously loaded after, which worked only by timing
luck via loadModel()'s async gap). renderKpis() now calls
TSMKpiCards.render() instead of hand-rolled card HTML, with a fallback
path if the module fails to load.

Not yet wired: Decision Engine / Workflow Engine into O2C's existing UI
(O2C's own runAnalysis()/engine flow already works, left untouched).
CRM, Approval, CPQ not yet touched -- same script-tag pattern applies
directly since they already load the same control-plane paths.

Smoke-tested locally: server boots, all new/fixed static files serve
200, /api/foundation/decision correctly 400s on unknown vertical,
o2c-war-room.html loads 200.
